War crimes in Ukraine: Police close investigation into murders in a street in Bucha
description: Ukrainian police have issued wanted notices for six Russian soldiers over the premeditated murder of 17 civilians in Bucha, a suburb of Kyiv, in 2022. In total, 378 bodies were found in the city.

Ceasefires in Gaza and Lebanon both favor Israel
description: In both cases, Israel has imposed a situation that more closely resembles a de-escalation or low-intensity conflict. But Israeli violations of the Gaza ceasefire have resulted in far more deaths.

headline: French court jails four Bulgarians for defacing Paris Holocaust memorial
description: The four perpetrators were sentenced to between two and four years in prison for their involvement in stencilling red handprints onto the memorial. Prosecutors think Russia was behind it.

headline: French lawmakers vote against wealth tax on super-rich
description: The proposal would impose a 2% tax on wealth over €100 million, which garnered a lot of popular support. It was proposed by economist Gabriel Zucman as a tool to help France balance its books.

headline: The French cities utterly transformed by Airbnb
description: 'The Airbnb Ogre' (3/6). Turning an apartment into short-term tourist accommodation may seem harmless. But on a large scale, it ends up transforming entire cities and daily life for their residents. France's politicians are trying to crack down on the system.

headline: Madagascar's new government faces scrutiny from Gen Z
description: President Michaël Randrianirina announced the 28 members of the government on Tuesday, October 28. Opposition leaders to the ousted regime, newcomers and technocrats now have 60 days to deliver results.

headline: Egypt opens Grand Egyptian Museum, centerpiece of its tourism industry
description: The colossal project dates back to the 1990s. The huge site, next to the pyramids of Giza, is billed as the largest museum in the world dedicated to a single civilization. It opens on November 1 after years of delays.
